# {{MODULE}}

Idempotent setup for **{{MODULE}}** — built on the `idempotent.sh` lib pattern (check → mutate-if-needed → re-verify).

## Use

```bash
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh help        # show usage
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh verify      # check current state, change nothing
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh install     # bring desired state into existence (safe to re-run)
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh cleanup     # reverse install (keeps persistent data)
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh purge       # cleanup + remove persistent data (confirms)
```

## Remote execution

The script runs locally by default. To target a remote host:

```bash
SSH_TARGET=admin@host SSH_PORT=2222 SSH_IDENTITY=~/.ssh/admin_key \
    bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh install
```

`run_cmd` inside the script transparently switches between local `bash -c` and `ssh ...` based on `SSH_TARGET`.

## Idempotence test

```bash
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh verify
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh install
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh install     # second run -- no [CHANGING] lines
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh cleanup
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh cleanup     # second run -- no [CHANGING] lines
bash setup-{{MODULE}}.sh install
```

Pass condition: every step exits 0, and the second `install` / second `cleanup` only print `[CHECKING] ... already correct` / `already absent` — never `[CHANGING]`.

## Configuration

Declarative parameters live in `config.json`; secrets do not. For local secrets use a `.secrets/` directory (gitignored); for shared infra use a secret manager.

